File: Over 3,800 people have tested positive for the virus in the last 24 hours. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says 69 more people, including a fourth teenager, have died from COVID-19 in the last 24 hours. This brings the country's death toll to 1,423. This is a 50 percent increase over the past seven days. The fatalities were recorded in the Western Cape (36), the Eastern Cape (9) and Gauteng (24). READ: SA's COVID-19 cases jump by 10,000 in five days Over 3,800 people have tested positive for the virus in the last 24 hours. Of those more than a thousand are from Gauteng. A total of 65,736 people have tested positive since the start of the outbreak and nearly 37,000 have already recovered. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.